Kano COVID-19 index case Ambassador Kabiru Rabiu has been discharged after testing negative twice. One of his sons, Malam Abba Rabiu, confirmed the discharge of his father to reporters on Sunday. The Nation reports Rabiu became the index case of COVID-19 in Kano on April 11 at a private hospital in the metropolis. He said the former diplomat was discharged from Kwanar Dawaki Isolation centre on Sunday morning. Malam Abba Rabiu, while thanking God over the health position of his father , also prayed for the speedy recovery of others.